Cardio 👉🏽only burn during the session and it depends on what type, the after-burn is inferior compared to resistance training.  Muscle mass will not increase or may even be catabolic, so no metabolic improvements.

👉🏽Resistance training burns more during and post and is the only way to IMPROVE your metabolism.  The goal for long term fitness is to improve your body composition.

3 tips for this fluff season 🤓

1.  Prioritize strength training over cardio.  Resistance training builds muscles which in turn increases the metabolism, therefore burning more calories at rest.  Cardiovascular training only increases the metabolic rate during the session.  Using a PreWorkout such as Prevail will improve your performance. 

2. Prioritize protein consumption over carbs and fats.  This is the only nutrient your body needs to build & repair.  Carbs & fats are energy, if not used then your body will store it as body fat.  Use carbs mainly around training for energy and some fats to stay full later in the day.  Adding premium protein shakes daily such as Total Iso makes it easy, low calorie & economical to hit your goals. 

3. Drink lots of water, at least 3 liters a day to keep you full, hydrated, and functioning optimally.
